Vice President Joe Biden spoke with Ukrainian President Petro Poroshenko to discuss Ukraine's financial and energy situation, as well as developments in eastern Ukraine. They discussed Ukraine's declaration of a ceasefire on December 9, which has reduced casualties. President Poroshenko updated the Vice President on Ukraine's financial situation and commitment to implementing reforms, including measures to combat corruption. The Vice President assured that the United States will work with international partners, including the International Monetary Fund, to provide macroeconomic support to Ukraine. Both leaders urged Russia to stop its separatist proxies from blocking the delivery of humanitarian aid to conflict-affected regions in eastern Ukraine.